Jimmy Anderson became England's leading wicket-taker in Test match cricket on Friday . 
  Anderson took the wicket of Denesh Ramdin in his 100th Test in Antigua . 
  Sir Ian Botham held the previous record of 383 wickets for England . 
  Botham was watching the Test from the commentary box . 
  Anderson claimed his 384th wicket in the first Test against West Indies . 
 